metadata.name: FACT_EVENT_LOGS
metadata.comment: This table contains flattened event logs from transactions on the Optimism Blockchain. Transactions may have multiple events, which are denoted by the event index for a transaction hash. Therefore, this table is unique on the combination of transaction hash and event index. Event names are decoded in this table where possible. The event inputs column will contain the log details in JSON format. Specific fields can be pulled from this column using the following sample format: ```event_inputs:<FILED_NAME>::<DATA TYPE> as <FIELD_NAME>```.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed. This field will not be unique in this table, as a given transaction can include multiple events.

ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.name: ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE
ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.comment: The function signature of this transaction.

ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The from address of this transaction.

ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.comment: The to address of this transaction.

CONTRACT_ADDRESS.name: CONTRACT_ADDRESS
CONTRACT_ADDRESS.comment: The address interacted with for a given event.

CONTRACT_NAME.name: CONTRACT_NAME
CONTRACT_NAME.comment: The name of the contract or token, where possible.

EVENT_NAME.name: EVENT_NAME
EVENT_NAME.comment: The decoded event name for a given event.

EVENT_INPUTS.name: EVENT_INPUTS
EVENT_INPUTS.comment: The decoded event inputs for a given event.

EVENT_REMOVED.name: EVENT_REMOVED
EVENT_REMOVED.comment: Whether the event has been removed from the transaction.

_LOG_ID.name: _LOG_ID
_LOG_ID.comment: This is the primary key for this table. This is a concatenation of the transaction hash and the event index at which the event occurred.

has_stats.description: Indicates whether there are statistics for this table

metadata.name: FACT_BLOCKS
metadata.comment: This table contains block level data for the Optimism Blockchain. This table can be used to analyze trends at a block level, for example gas fees vs. total transactions over time. For more information on EVM transactions, please see [Etherscan Resources](https://etherscan.io/directory/Learning_Resources/Ethereum) or [The Ethereum Organization](https://ethereum.org/en/developers/docs/blocks/)

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

NETWORK.name: NETWORK
NETWORK.comment: The network on the blockchain used by a transaction.

BLOCKCHAIN.name: BLOCKCHAIN
BLOCKCHAIN.comment: The blockchain on which transactions are being confirmed.

TX_COUNT.name: TX_COUNT
TX_COUNT.comment: Total number of transactions within a block.

DIFFICULTY.comment: The effort required to mine the block.

TOTAL_DIFFICULTY.name: TOTAL_DIFFICULTY
TOTAL_DIFFICULTY.comment: Total difficulty of the chain at a given block.

EXTRA_DATA.name: EXTRA_DATA
EXTRA_DATA.comment: Any data included by the validator for a given block.

GAS_LIMIT.name: GAS_LIMIT
GAS_LIMIT.comment: Total gas limit provided by all transactions in the block.

GAS_USED.name: GAS_USED
GAS_USED.comment: Total gas used in the block.

HASH.name: HASH
HASH.comment: The hash of the block header for a given block.

PARENT_HASH.name: PARENT_HASH
PARENT_HASH.comment: The hash of the block from which a given block is generated. Also known as the parent block.

RECEIPTS_ROOT.name: RECEIPTS_ROOT
RECEIPTS_ROOT.comment: The root of the state trie.

SHA3_UNCLES.name: SHA3_UNCLES
SHA3_UNCLES.comment: The mechanism which Ethereum Javascript RLP encodes an empty string.

SIZE.name: SIZE
SIZE.comment: Block size, which is determined by a given block's gas limit.

UNCLE_BLOCKS.name: UNCLE_BLOCKS
UNCLE_BLOCKS.comment: Uncle blocks occur when two blocks are mined and broadcasted at the same time, with the same block number. The block validated across the most nodes will be added to the primary chain, and the other one becomes an uncle block. Miners do receive rewards for uncle blocks.

BLOCK_HEADER_JSON.comment: This JSON column contains the block header details.

FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The sending address of this trace. This is not necessarily the from address of the transaction.

TO_ADDRESS.name: TO_ADDRESS

DATA.name: DATA
DATA.comment: The raw JSON data for this trace.

SUB_TRACES.name: SUB_TRACES
SUB_TRACES.comment: The amount of nested sub traces for this trace.

metadata.name: EZ_POOL_DETAILS
metadata.comment: This table contains metadata details for liquidity pools on Velodrome.

POOL_ADDRESS.name: POOL_ADDRESS
POOL_ADDRESS.comment: The address of the liquidity pool.

POOL_NAME.name: POOL_NAME
POOL_NAME.comment: The name of the liquidity pool.

POOL_TYPE.name: POOL_TYPE
POOL_TYPE.comment: The type of liquidity pool, either stable or volatile. Stable pools are designed for assets which have little to no volatility. Volatile pools are designed for assets with high price volatility, and use a generic AMM formula.

TOKEN0_SYMBOL.name: TOKEN0_SYMBOL
TOKEN0_SYMBOL.comment: The symbol of token0 in the pool.

TOKEN1_SYMBOL.name: TOKEN1_SYMBOL
TOKEN1_SYMBOL.comment: The symbol of token1 in the pool.

TOKEN0_ADDRESS.name: TOKEN0_ADDRESS
TOKEN0_ADDRESS.comment: The address of token0 in the pool.

TOKEN1_ADDRESS.name: TOKEN1_ADDRESS
TOKEN1_ADDRESS.comment: The address of token1 in the pool.

TOKEN0_DECIMALS.name: TOKEN0_DECIMALS
TOKEN0_DECIMALS.comment: The decimals of token0 in the pool.

TOKEN1_DECIMALS.name: TOKEN1_DECIMALS
TOKEN1_DECIMALS.comment: The decimals of token1 in the pool.

CREATED_TIMESTAMP.name: CREATED_TIMESTAMP
CREATED_TIMESTAMP.comment: The timestamp the pool was created.

CREATED_BLOCK.name: CREATED_BLOCK
CREATED_BLOCK.comment: The block at which the pool was created.

CREATED_HASH.name: CREATED_HASH
CREATED_HASH.comment: The tx hash in which the pool was created.

metadata.name: FACT_HOURLY_TOKEN_PRICES
metadata.comment: This table contains the hourly USD prices for tokens on the Optimism blockchain.

HOUR.name: HOUR
HOUR.comment: The hour the token price was recorded.

TOKEN_ADDRESS.name: TOKEN_ADDRESS
TOKEN_ADDRESS.comment: The Optimism contract address for this token.

PRICE.name: PRICE
PRICE.comment: The average hourly price for this token.

IS_IMPUTED.name: IS_IMPUTED
IS_IMPUTED.comment: This column denotes if we carried forward the last recorded price in order to fill hourly gaps from the source.

metadata.name: EZ_CLAIMED_REWARDS
metadata.comment:
This table contains details about claimed rewards on Velodrome. Rewards are paid to VELO lockers, LP token stakers, and veVELO voters. Please use the `reward_type` column to analyze the different types of claimed rewards.

`venft_distribution` -> paid to VELO lockers
`lp_reward` -> paid to LP token stakers
`voter_rewards` -> paid to locked VELO votes

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed.

ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.name: ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE
ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.comment: The function signature of this transaction.

ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The from address of this transaction.

ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.comment: The to address of this transaction.

CONTRACT_ADDRESS.name: CONTRACT_ADDRESS
CONTRACT_ADDRESS.comment: The contract address interacted with in this event.

EVENT_INDEX.name: EVENT_INDEX
EVENT_INDEX.comment: The event index within the transaction.

REWARD_TYPE.name: REWARD_TYPE
REWARD_TYPE.comment: The type of rewards claimed, either `voter_rewards`, `venft_distribution`, or `lp_reward`.

TOKEN_ID.name: TOKEN_ID
TOKEN_ID.comment: The veNFT token ID. Only applies to veNFT distributions.

CLAIMED_AMOUNT.name: CLAIMED_AMOUNT
CLAIMED_AMOUNT.comment: The amount of tokens claimed, decimal adjusted.

CLAIMED_AMOUNT_USD.name: CLAIMED_AMOUNT_USD
CLAIMED_AMOUNT_USD.comment: The amount of tokens claimed, in USD.

TOKEN_SYMBOL.name: TOKEN_SYMBOL
TOKEN_SYMBOL.comment: The symbol of the claimed tokens.

TOKEN_ADDRESS.name: TOKEN_ADDRESS
TOKEN_ADDRESS.comment: The contract address of the claimed tokens

CLAIM_EPOCH.name: CLAIM_EPOCH
CLAIM_EPOCH.comment: The claim epoch, only applicable to veNFT distributions.

MAX_EPOCH.name: MAX_EPOCH
MAX_EPOCH.comment: The max epoch, only applicable to veNFT distributions.
